President Trump delivered remarks at the opening of the new Louis Vuitton workshop in Alvarado, Texas. He expressed gratitude to President Erdogan of Turkey and the Kurdish leadership for their assistance in achieving a ceasefire in Syria. The President also praised the work of Vice President Pence and Secretary of State Pompeo. He highlighted the success of his administration in combating ISIS and creating jobs in the United States. The President thanked Bernard Arnault, Chairman and CEO of Louis Vuitton, for his investment in Texas and for bringing manufacturing jobs back to America. He emphasized his commitment to American manufacturing and the growth of the economy. The President also announced that Louis Vuitton has signed the Pledge to American Workers, committing to provide job opportunities for the workers in Texas. He concluded by cutting the ribbon and officially welcoming Louis Vuitton to Texas.